# Backend .NET — Conventions

## Architecture

- 4-layer Clean Architecture: Core → Application → Infrastructure → Api
- Core does NOT reference any other project
- Project names: `LegalAiAr.{Layer}` (Api, Application, Core, Infrastructure, Agents, AgentEvals)

## Patterns

- CQRS with MediatR in Application
- Minimal API in Api (NO Controllers)
- Central Package Management via `Directory.Packages.props`
- Tests with xUnit + NSubstitute + FluentAssertions

## Azure naming

- Resources: `{service}-legal-ai-ar-{environment}` (e.g., `sql-legal-ai-ar-dev`)
- Database: `LegalAiAr`
- Storage containers: kebab-case

## Entities

- Entities live in `LegalAiAr.Core/Entities/`
- Follow the ontology model in `docs/ontology/argentine-legal-ontology.md`
- Use `Guid` as the ID type
- Include `CreatedAt` and `UpdatedAt` on every entity

## Language rule (strict)

- **Everything in English**: code (variables, methods, classes, interfaces, enums), file names, tables, indexes, storage, URLs, endpoints, DTOs, domain entities, commits, technical documentation, code comments.
- **Spanish only for**: end-user facing messages in the app (UI labels, error messages, tooltips, user-visible content).
- Example: class is `LegalNorm`, table is `LegalNorms`, endpoint is `/api/legal-norms`, but the UI label says "Normas Legales".

## Reminder

- Do not create code directly unless the user requests it
